<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by djavulkai:
[B]Ah...good.  =)

thillian: 

&gt;&gt;Think about this: What if all the enemies you had to kill were also extremely easy and more plentiful? &lt;&lt;

You only argue your point to the extreme.  No mature gamer has ever said "I want to be able to solo Sol B with my Warrior".  Simply, though, it should be less of a challenge when fending off monsters that are 15 levels below you.  

I am an avid player of D&D and also usually wind up being the DM (lack of options, really).  In D&D, your 15th level character could walk into an orc camp, waste around 20-30 orcs and walk out with a few minor bruises.  In EQ, you would get slaughtered.  The scope of the game is really centered around the players being some sort of adventurer, but not a hero, which is a common mistake made by many.  The real problem lies in the fact that it is hard to believe that as the character grows in power, they can still be beaten by low level mobs.  Do you think that a Mist Wolf should take down a 25th level mage with no pet?  I have seen it happen.

In any case, my point is that the game ought to be evened out a bit more.  At 26th level, i still and kinda afraid of going into BlackBurrow, even though i would not get exp for ~anything~ there, they can still wipe the floor with me.

"That ain't right"[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
